    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a dry large, <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a matching lid over a medium heat</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>coriander seeds</strong>, cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant, set aside and reserve the pan</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk so they don’t burn!</p>",
